cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with the robustness of neural networks against adversarial attacks. It could also belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as it discusses the vulnerability of neural networks to adversarial attacks. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision) as adversarial attacks are a common problem in image classification tasks. It could also be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it deals with the robustness of neural networks.
